> Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Indonesian Style Satay Extra Chicken Salad in just 20 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

Bring a #large saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil on high heat. Halve the @salad potatoes{350%g}(halved, no need to peel).

When your pan of water is boiling, add the potatoes and simmer until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%mins}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{390%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything cooks, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated, or use a garlic press). Boil a half-full #kettle{} for the dressing.

Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened #sachet{} using a #rolling pin{}.

Trim the @cucumber{1/2}(trimmed and cut into 1cm wide strips, then cut into 1cm pieces widthways), then halve lengthways.

Halve the @lime{1}(halved).

Meanwhile, add the @peanut butter{30%g} and @boiled water{2%tbsp} for the dressing in a #large bowl{} and mix until it makes a smooth paste.

Stir in the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g} and squeeze all the juice from the lime into the dressing bowl. Combine until the peanut butter has dissolved to make a smooth dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the chicken is cooked, add the @Indonesian style spice mix{1%sachet} and garlic to the pan, stir-fry for ~{1%min}.

Once the potatoes are ready, drain in a #colander{} then add to the chicken.

Next, stir in the @honey{1%tbsp}. Toss the chicken and potatoes until evenly coated and remove from the heat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When everything's ready, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g}, cucumber and cooked chicken and potatoes to the satay dressing bowl. Toss together and share out between your #serving bowls{}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Sprinkle over the peanuts to finish. Enjoy!